      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WILL TO EXCEL (2) tough old gelding who looks well placed in this contest. Stalked the good tempo with a game third over 2100m at Gosford. Goes well at this trip and expected to go close. BLAZING GURU (3) getting up to her right trip and set to peak fifth-up. Gripped on late with the 60kg with a respectable fifth over 2100m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Was a month between runs on that occasion and strips fitter for this. TAVIJEWEL (6) mixing his form this prep and gets in light with Quince's 2kg claim. Anchored with the 58kg with a plugging sixth over 2000m at Canberra. Maps well and shapes as a top-three player. SHYLOCK (7) sharp improver at the big odds with a slashing second over 2000m at Canberra in BM55 class. Hard to beat in this suitable race.",
